# CODEOWNERS — the human-sign-off boundary for the agent loop (ADR-0006).
#
# Paths listed here are NEVER auto-merged, regardless of green CI. These are the
# load-bearing decisions: kernel semantics, stable identity, the document format,
# the seam interfaces, and the durable spec itself. Everything else may flow
# through the tiered autonomy process.
#
# Reviewers: @theironchef (add more as the team grows).

# The durable spec — changing intent requires a human.
/docs/adr/                     @theironchef
/CLAUDE.md                     @theironchef

# The seam interfaces — widening or adding a seam is a human decision.
/src/gitcad/seams.py           @theironchef

# Stable identity — foundational; changes need a migration story.
/src/gitcad/identity.py        @theironchef

# The document/text format — geometric-semver surface.
/src/gitcad/document.py        @theironchef

# The Part standard — the cross-domain interchange contract (ADR-0008/9).
# The most change-resistant surface gitcad owns; schema changes need migrations.
/src/gitcad/part/              @theironchef

# Kernel semantics — geometry output changes are breaking by definition.
/src/gitcad/kernel/            @theironchef

# The permanent test tiers are the real specification.
/tests/invariants/             @theironchef
/tests/golden/                 @theironchef

# The autonomy/security machinery of the loop itself.
/src/gitcad/report/            @theironchef
